/** @format */export var CVDesc=['A French native, Yannick received his formal culinary training in a renowned Michelin-starred restaurant in Lille at the age of 16 and apprenticed in Pastry. He developed a profound culinary knowledge in the kitchen with a specialisation in pastry, before taking up his first chef de cuisine position at the Regal Kowloon Hotel in Hong Kong at the age of 27.','Chef Yannick has more than 30 years of experience, with exposure working in Europe, Asia and the Middle East. This has allowed him to develop a comprehensive understanding of Asian and international cuisines, both classical and modern, which he delivers with gourmet flair.','Most recently Executive Chef at Morgan Stanley Hong Kong from December 2008 to April 2022, chef Yannick’s role saw him manage his team in a corporate environment. This included working on a broad range of events, from business lunches to summits and conferences for both internal and external stakeholders across the APAC region.'];export var CVApproach=['Client first; understands the objectives, core values and vision of the company','Follows and adheres to the principle of think, do, measure, correct and improve continuously','Result-oriented, adopt actions to circumstances to obtain the best possible results','Creates a dynamic structure in the kitchen; focuses on fresh seasonal products, quality processes and resources','Hands-on; coaches and leads a team to bring out the best in its members; experienced in team building and training','Adept at managing budgets and achieving targets'];export var CVFuture='Looking for opportunities based in Hong Kong or the APAC region overseeing sites in a Corporate, Hospitality, or Sports & Leisure working environment in which to deliver first-class meals that take nutritional value and customer needs into account.';export var ExpItems=[{title:'Executive Chef',loc:'Morgan Stanley (Sodexo), Hong Kong',period:'December 2008 – April 2022 (13 years and 4 months)',img:'ms-HKG.jpg',link:'https://www.morganstanley.com/about-us/global-offices/asia-pacific/hong-kong',cert:['morgan04.png','morgan02.png','thankyouLetter.png'],certDesc:['Recommendation Letter by Operations Director Raymond Moore','10 Years Long Term Service Award',"Thank You emails from Executive Director, Morgan Stanley Marketing Jeanne Zee"],desc:"In charge of the in-house culinary team of 22 chefs at Morgan Stanley’s ICC office, which spans 15 floors: L30 to L47 and L86, including managing daily food operation and offerings for approximately 3,000 Morgan Stanley employees, with on-site production of dishes spanning Chinese, Japanese, Indian, Western and South-East Asian cuisines.",ach:["Supervise and ensure all services meet client’s standards and expectations at all times and for all outlets operating breakfast, lunch, afternoon tea and dinner","Manage ongoing culinary theme promotions featuring different cuisines to keep patronage high, with a total of 1,800 transactions daily","Coordinate two teams to operate various amenities including: Outlet team in charge of Mosaicc restaurant, coffee bar and lounge, two traders’ pantries, one floor of corporate service (L86); and Catering team in charge of Executive Floor and Conference Centre.","Create broad and robust food portfolio and deliver meals for internal and external business and corporate events including to Executive Floor, which offers numerous business set lunches, cocktail receptions, buffets, bento set menus and various cuisines across 16 meeting rooms, 12 training rooms, and an amphitheatre accommodating up to 120 guests","2009 – Pre-opening phase, planned and implemented F&B budgets, recruiting, training, HSE standard and menu offering","2010 – Planned and designed pastry room","2010 – Coordinated corporate event with Jean-Francois Piege in Singapore","2010 – Staff development – team member participated in the Sodexo World Class Chef programme in Boston, US","2010–2020 – Part of annual Asia Pacific and annual summit conference for Morgan Stanley, Hong Kong and Singapore","2010–2020 – Coordinated corporate events with celebrity chefs in Hong Kong, China, India, France and Singapore","2010–2020 – Continuously supported Sodexo and Morgan Stanley with sourcing from WWF sustainable fisheries and reducing carbon footprint","2011 – Part of the culinary exchange programme for Sodexo Prestige, Paris (Microsoft / Canal+ / MEDEF)","2011 – Led staff development in which a pastry chef successfully obtained the certificate of pastry from Germany and VTC Hong Kong","2011 – Coordinated with Pierre Gagnaire for a VIP menu Lunch for 350 guests, and a dinner for 20 guests in Singapore","2012–2018 – Part of the Sodexo Global chef programme with major clients in Shanghai, Boston and Manila (Johnson & Johnson / Microsoft / Fordham)"]},{title:'Executive Sous-Chef',loc:'Fota Island Resort (Sheraton), Cork, Ireland',period:'May 2006 – November 2008 (2 years and 6 months)',img:'fota-IRE.jpg',link:'https://www.fotaisland.ie/',cert:['sheraton.png'],certDesc:['Recommendation Letter by Executive Chef Neil Foster'],desc:"In charge of daily operations at the 130-room resort, including breakfast, lunch and dinner, and menu planning for the two restaurants, banqueting facilities for up to 250 covers, and room service for the outlets. In charge of full operations during the absence of the Executive Chef.",ach:["Pre-opening kitchen-hotel team","Management and organisation of the kitchens with a staff of 25 chefs and 7 stewards","Ensure kitchen operations adhere to the HACCP system","Recruitment and training of new staff members","Develop menu concept based on Mediterranean cooking style","Execute smooth running operations of the fine dining restaurant","2006 food cost target of 28.4%; achieved 27.5%"]},{title:'Chef de Cuisine',loc:'Arabian Court, One & Only Royal Mirage, Dubai, UAE',period:'November 2002 – November 2005 (3 years)',img:'OneOnly-DBI.jpg',link:'https://www.oneandonlyresorts.com/royal-mirage',cert: